
[1]improperly

   IMPROP'ERLY, adv. Not fitly; in a manner not suited to the end; in a
   manner not suited to the company, time, place and circumstances;
   unsuitably; incongruously.

   1. In a manner not according with established usages; inaccurately;
   ungrammatically; as, to speak or write improperly.
